features.name: Aldedh Catalyzes the NADPH-dependent reduction of L-glutamate 5-phosphate into L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde and phosphate. The product spontaneously undergoes cyclization to form 1-pyrroline-5- carboxylate
AA_kinase,PUA Catalyzes the transfer of a phosphate group to glutamate to form L-glutamate 5-phosphate
Porin_1 Belongs to the Gram-negative porin family

Crl Binds to the sigma-S subunit of RNA polymerase, activating expression of sigma-S-regulated genes. Stimulates RNA polymerase holoenzyme formation and may bind to several other sigma factors, such as sigma-70 and sigma-32
DUF1100 Displays esterase activity toward pNP-butyrate
Pribosyltran Acts on guanine, xanthine and to a lesser extent hypoxanthine

M20_dimer,Peptidase_M20 Dipeptidase with broad substrate specificity. Requires dipeptide substrates with an unblocked N-terminus and the amino group in the alpha or beta position. Non-protein amino acids and proline are not accepted in the C-terminal position, whereas some dipeptide amides and formyl amino acids are hydrolyzed. Also shows cysteinylglycinase activity, which is sufficient for E.coli to utilize cysteinylglycine as a cysteine source

IMS,IMS_C,IMS_HHH Poorly processive, error-prone DNA polymerase involved in untargeted mutagenesis. Copies undamaged DNA at stalled replication forks, which arise in vivo from mismatched or misaligned primer ends. These misaligned primers can be extended by PolIV. Exhibits no 3'-5' exonuclease (proofreading) activity. May be involved in translesional synthesis, in conjunction with the beta clamp from PolIII
SIS_2 Catalyzes the isomerization of sedoheptulose 7-phosphate in D-glycero-D-manno-heptose 7-phosphate

Acyl-CoA_dh_1,Acyl-CoA_dh_M,Acyl-CoA_dh_N,DUF1974 Catalyzes the dehydrogenation of acyl-coenzymes A (acyl- CoAs) to 2-enoyl-CoAs, the first step of the beta-oxidation cycle of fatty acid degradation. Is required for

CN_hydrolase Hydrolyzes alpha-ketoglutaramate (a-KGM) to alpha- ketoglutarate (alpha-KG) and ammonia, has weak activity on L- glutamine, almost no activity on deaminated glutathione (dGSH) and none on glutathione (By similarity). May function as a metabolite repair enzyme (By similarity)
GerE,Response_reg Response regulator containing a CheY-like receiver domain and an HTH DNA-binding domain
Biotin_lipoyl_2,HlyD,HlyD_3 HlyD membrane-fusion protein of T1SS
PapB Adhesin biosynthesis transcription regulatory protein
